                    'Write a query that sorts employees by a custom priority order: CEOs first, then Directors, then Managers, then all other job titles alphabetically.',
                    "Using CASE WHEN without GROUP BY, write a query that shows for each employee a column <code>tenure_category</code>: 'Veteran' (hired before 2018), 'Experienced' (2018-2021), 'New Hire' (after 2021). Then, write a second query using GROUP BY on this CASE WHEN expression to count employees in each category.\n\n---",
